					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3167993#post-3558938</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3167993/scp-3070#post-3558938</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 27 Jul 2017 09:32:44 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>NatVoltaic</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2800867</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Note that this was written without an explanation being needed to enjoy this, but here's the general author canon:</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;SPOILERS</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>SCP-3070-1 is some sort of alien that is attempting to take the solar system over. It's method is by using some weird form of technology that will generate itself at other locations, trying to adapt its body to suit locations. However, it thinks that the names of places (such as the asteroids) are semi-literal descriptions of them, which leads to things getting weird when it tries to adapt and colonize.</p> <p>The displayed text is meant to hint at this and the unusual technologies it is using.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3167993#post-3558925</guid>
